<div id="review_609688843" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/609688843" />
    <a title="Mohammed Arabey" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13592557-mohammed-arabey"><img alt="Mohammed Arabey" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1364338486p2/13592557.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/609688843?book_show_action=true">May 07, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mohammed Arabey" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mohammed Arabey" href="/user/show/13592557-mohammed-arabey">Mohammed Arabey</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer609688843" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7478259554684854805"><b>Her 10th Birthday came with a strange present..<br/>She received a strange book..The Book of Shadows..<br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1384514106i/6892040.jpg' width='357' height='228' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>Which was the beginning of a series of Strange Fantasy events..<br/>A High in the cloud Library..<br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1384507489i/6890520.jpg' width='355' height='210' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>An Old Medieval Castle full of secrets... and Ghosts..<br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1384507834i/6890563._SX540_.jpg' width='355' height='206' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>..located near a traditional Gypsy&apos;s Camp<br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1384508243i/6890657._SX540_.jpg' width='355' height='206' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>And an old time legendry conflict..Between 2 peoples..<br/>Between 2 different civilizations, India &amp; Atlantis.. <br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1384509397i/6890839._SX540_.jpg' width='355' height='200' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1384509397i/6890840.jpg' width='355' height='208' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>All that and even much more fantasy we can read and live with Nirupa,her mother and friends..along with her </b></span>
  <span id="freeText7478259554684854805" style="display:none"><b>Her 10th Birthday came with a strange present..<br>She received a strange book..The Book of Shadows..<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1384514106i/6892040.jpg" width="357" height="228" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>Which was the beginning of a series of Strange Fantasy events..<br>A High in the cloud Library..<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1384507489i/6890520.jpg" width="355" height="210" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>An Old Medieval Castle full of secrets... and Ghosts..<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1384507834i/6890563._SX540_.jpg" width="355" height="206" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>..located near a traditional Gypsy's Camp<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1384508243i/6890657._SX540_.jpg" width="355" height="206" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>And an old time legendry conflict..Between 2 peoples..<br>Between 2 different civilizations, India &amp; Atlantis.. <br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1384509397i/6890839._SX540_.jpg" width="355" height="200" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1384509397i/6890840.jpg" width="355" height="208" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>All that and even much more fantasy we can read and live with Nirupa,her mother and friends..along with her little fairy..<br><br><u>The Story</u> is really fun..specially with the involve of a nice fantasy origin of Atlantis,The Lost City..and the ancient India and the fantasy about their habitats.<br>But there's something bothered me that I can't put my finger on, but I totally think that's all me, since I didn't like the "Fantasy Overdose" <br>The Fantasy here is almost "extreme" with fairies, spells, potions, Santa, even Vampire!! ,Ghosts, Astral Projection "that scene start so creepy which I loved so much, but fall later into another extreme fantasy"</b><br>May be it's because I'm getting old -30 now :(- which would be not the novel's fault ,as well the fact I'm not ebook reader "This is the FIRST over 75 pages novel I've ever read in ebook edition, that's why I took from me long time" ...or another fact that only one fantasy I felt so perfect..that I keep compare with like all the time..<b>
  <i>The Harry Potter Curse</i>
</b> that affect me....<br>May be cause the setting of the story feel normal -normal as the environment where Harry Potter start his journey- but an extreme fantasy dose mix with it without limits or controlled by a law -like the rules between wizard and witches and the muggles-<br>I think it may deserve 4+ stars if you're younger than me or read for your children..<b><br><br> But anyway it didn't stop me of thinking that the novel is really fun journey specially because of <br><u>The Setting</u> which as I said before was so nice,the Castle specially was my favorite.,also the Gypsy camp..the story of Atlantis..That was well written as well as <br><u>The Characters</u> .. despite the fact that Ni's behavior annoying me sometimes -we the 80s generation think the new one a bit spoiled than us :) "check the American Reunion movie :)"- I still love how the author draw her with real love and passion, which at many times you'd touch how innocence is she and her loving and caring for her friends and family. <br>The surprise ending was nice, when I look back I find it's fit which is nice.<br><br>Finally <br>*******<br>it's the debut of Ni..As well as the author who's got a very well fantasy tools and -since she herself the translator to English- a very very lovely way of telling story with easy language.<br></b>"I've noticed some expressions that almost like the Arabic ones,which was really nice"<b><br>I loved the mix between magic and fantasy and real world and this quote made me think it's a real good blending <br><blockquote>"So, Grandma," Melissa asked in bewilderment, "Is there nothing magic here?"<br>"It is not the plants but the mind that makes the magic," Grandmother said.<br> "These are popular names given to plants a long time ago. Thus, lizard’s tail is a kind of herb I grow in my garden. The mare’s legs are just fresh clovers. The devil’s milk is wartgrass; the cat’s intestines are a kind of pods. Did you think, Nirupa, to make magic, we have to stab a poor cat? Then," she continued, "Blood fingers are cupflowers. I can give those to you as well. The eyes of ox are <br>dried marigold flowers. You will find it difficult to find the dragon’s clutches because they do not grow during this season, but I think I have some left in a jar in my kitchen."</blockquote>
<br> But still at other times the mix was not that perfect for me.. and some plot lines felt like overdose of fantasy or a bit "filler" that was better to just remove and focused more into the core of the wonderful setup of the main plot and the setting.<br><br>I wish the next part will be stronger..cause YES I'd love to read more for Nirupa and the author assure to me that there's a sequel for Ni and her friends when they're older.<br>That must be fun..</b><i> and I wish to buy it in Hardcover edition that'd be better for me :) and wish this one get into this edition soon too </i> <br><b><br>So to more stories for Nirupa..our new witch <br> <img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1384522523i/6894018.jpg" width="357" height="238" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br>Mohammed Arabey<br>10th November 2013</b></span>
