        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer605885243" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10028277457698765181">Ok, To start with, this book is a &quot;diamond in the rough&quot;. I found this book completely by chance when I was browsin to find books similar to the &quot;House of Secrets&quot;. <br/>I was surprised. How come such a book has not become an immedate sucess? Nirupa and the Book of Shadows is a wonderful read that takes you to a beautifully crafted world of magic, mystery, values and friendship. It is well-written, funny and interesting. THe characters are well - developped and engaging. I could see them and feel wha</span>
  <span id="freeText10028277457698765181" style="display:none">Ok, To start with, this book is a "diamond in the rough". I found this book completely by chance when I was browsin to find books similar to the "House of Secrets". <br />I was surprised. How come such a book has not become an immedate sucess? Nirupa and the Book of Shadows is a wonderful read that takes you to a beautifully crafted world of magic, mystery, values and friendship. It is well-written, funny and interesting. THe characters are well - developped and engaging. I could see them and feel what they were feeling. The story itself is so intersting. The girl, Ni lives with her mother in a small town. Her mother is single mom who is very much protective of her daughter. Ni rebells about it, but she cannot do much. On the day of her birthday though, something unusual happenes. Ni receives a very strange book as a birthday gift sent by her father, about whom she doesn't know anyting. It turns out that her father is a powerfull magician, the only descendent survived of the ancient Atlantis and a follower of back magic. Her mother on the other hand is a powerfull magician of opposing sides. Ni was born to fullfill a grim and mysterious prophecy and bring back Atlantis on Earth. The story develops quickly with the family moving on to Spain to live in a castle that previously belonged to Ni's father and that Ni inerits after news reach the family that her father has suddenly died in a car accident. There are amazing twists and turns in the story that keep you hooked. I finished the book in two afternoons. I couldn't put it down. I will definitely recommend it to all of my froends. <br />And, yes, of course the ending is surprising. </span>
