<div id="review_614828081" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/614828081" />
    <a title="Kyla" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9625761-kyla"><img alt="Kyla" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1479595099p2/9625761.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/614828081?book_show_action=true">May 13, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kyla" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kyla" href="/user/show/9625761-kyla">Kyla</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9625761-kyla?shelf=ebooks">ebooks</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer614828081" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1545333784706348448">I take it that this book has amazed me very well. Fantasies have always been in my liking. <br/><br/>Nirupa, as a young and innocent child, discovers new things about herself and her family by the time she receives the Book of Shadows. She is, however, an inquisitive child, and her curiosity leads her to dangers and revelations. <br/><br/>Such adventures hooked me into the story with twists of histories bound together. No matter how different the characters were, the connection remains intact. Not every part was ex</span>
  <span id="freeText1545333784706348448" style="display:none">I take it that this book has amazed me very well. Fantasies have always been in my liking. <br /><br />Nirupa, as a young and innocent child, discovers new things about herself and her family by the time she receives the Book of Shadows. She is, however, an inquisitive child, and her curiosity leads her to dangers and revelations. <br /><br />Such adventures hooked me into the story with twists of histories bound together. No matter how different the characters were, the connection remains intact. Not every part was exciting, though. <br /><br /><blockquote> "We live in bad times. People do harm to those they<br />don’t understand. There is nothing worse than a closed mind and the blind trust that you are the only person to be right." </blockquote> <br /><br />This quote is well-thought-of, so it has stayed in my mind after I finished the book. It reflects to how people see others. The blind refers to the community who don't actually see and understand what really is in front of them that results to wrong conclusions. If you would observe the characters' actions, you can see that it is one of the main causes of their doings.<br /><br />The ending clearly surprised me. I always like it when the unexpected happens. Nonetheless, if you would look back and carefully consider the little things that had happened, there are clues. :)<br /><br />Despite the difficulties of the English language, the author has shown her efforts in writing notably since the book was first published in the Albanian language last 2007.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1545333784706348448" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
